title: Panel, 1701–50
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: punto in aria needle lace
creditline: Bequest of Richard Cranch Greenleaf in memory of his mother, Adeline Emma Greenleaf
description: Design consists of a large basket filled with floral and foliated forms. The basket seems to have been cut from a large flounce to fit into the oval top of a mirror. Fond: brides bouclée; Modes: venises, portes, gaze quadrillée, Point Mignon, réseau mouché, St. Esprit avec rangs clairs.
